================================================================================
RESONANCE STRUCTURE VISUALIZER - COMPLETE INSTALLATION GUIDE
================================================================================

This guide provides EVERY command and software needed to run this project
on a fresh computer from scratch. as a reference, this is made with ai after inputting all code in, needed this to figure out what do download on other laptop

================================================================================
PART 1: ONE-TIME SOFTWARE INSTALLATION
================================================================================

-------------------------------------------
1. INSTALL PYTHON 3.8+
-------------------------------------------

Windows:
  1. Visit: https://www.python.org/downloads/
  2. Download latest Python 3.x
  3. Run installer
  4. ✅ CHECK "Add Python to PATH"
  5. Click "Install Now"
  6. Verify:
     python --version

Mac:
  brew install python3

Linux (Ubuntu/Debian):
  sudo apt update
  sudo apt install python3 python3-pip python3-venv

-------------------------------------------
2. INSTALL NODE.JS AND NPM
-------------------------------------------

Windows/Mac:
  1. Visit: https://nodejs.org/
  2. Download LTS version
  3. Run installer (npm included)
  4. Verify:
     node --version
     npm --version

Linux (Ubuntu/Debian):
  sudo apt update
  sudo apt install nodejs npm

-------------------------------------------
3. INSTALL GIT (OPTIONAL - for cloning)
-------------------------------------------

Windows:
  1. Visit: https://git-scm.com/download/win
  2. Download and install
  3. Use default options

Mac:
  brew install git

Linux:
  sudo apt install git

Verify:
  git --version

================================================================================
PART 2: GET PROJECT FILES
================================================================================

-------------------------------------------
OPTION A: Clone from GitHub
-------------------------------------------

cd Desktop
git clone https://github.com/YOUR-USERNAME/url.git
cd url

-------------------------------------------
OPTION B: Download ZIP
-------------------------------------------

1. Go to GitHub repository page
2. Click green "Code" button
3. Click "Download ZIP"
4. Extract to Desktop
5. Open terminal and navigate:
   cd Desktop/url

================================================================================
PART 3: BACKEND SETUP
================================================================================

-------------------------------------------
STEP 1: Navigate to Backend Folder
-------------------------------------------

cd backend

-------------------------------------------
STEP 2: Create Virtual Environment
-------------------------------------------

Windows:
  python -m venv venv

Mac/Linux:
  python3 -m venv venv

-------------------------------------------
STEP 3: Activate Virtual Environment
-------------------------------------------

Windows PowerShell:
  venv\Scripts\activate

Windows Command Prompt:
  venv\Scripts\activate.bat

Mac/Linux:
  source venv/bin/activate

NOTE: You should see (venv) before your prompt

-------------------------------------------
STEP 4: Install Python Dependencies
-------------------------------------------

pip install -r requirements.txt

This installs:
  - Flask 3.0.0 (Web framework)
  - Flask-CORS 4.0.0 (Cross-origin requests)
  - RDKit-PyPI 2022.9.5 (Chemistry toolkit)

If RDKit fails, try:
  pip install rdkit

-------------------------------------------
STEP 5: Start Backend Server
-------------------------------------------

python app.py

Expected output:
  * Running on http://127.0.0.1:5000
  * Debug mode: on

LEAVE THIS TERMINAL OPEN - Backend must keep running

Test in browser: http://localhost:5000/api/molecules
Should see JSON list of molecules

================================================================================
PART 4: FRONTEND SETUP
================================================================================

-------------------------------------------
STEP 1: Open NEW Terminal Window
-------------------------------------------

Keep backend terminal running!
Open second terminal/PowerShell

-------------------------------------------
STEP 2: Navigate to Frontend Folder
-------------------------------------------

cd Desktop/url/frontend

Adjust path based on where you extracted/cloned

-------------------------------------------
STEP 3: Install Node Dependencies
-------------------------------------------

npm install

This installs (takes 2-3 minutes):
  - React 18.2.0 (UI library)
  - React-DOM 18.2.0 (DOM rendering)
  - React-Scripts 5.0.1 (Build tools)
  - Axios 1.6.0 (HTTP client)
  - 3Dmol.js loaded via CDN (3D visualization)
  - Plus ~300 dependency packages

-------------------------------------------
STEP 4: Start Frontend Development Server
-------------------------------------------

npm start

Expected output:
  Compiled successfully!
  Local: http://localhost:3000

Browser should auto-open to localhost:3000

LEAVE THIS TERMINAL OPEN - Frontend must keep running

================================================================================
PART 5: VERIFY INSTALLATION
================================================================================

-------------------------------------------
Checklist - Both Servers Running
-------------------------------------------

Terminal 1 (Backend):
  ✅ Shows "Running on http://127.0.0.1:5000"
  ✅ (venv) visible in prompt
  ✅ No error messages

Terminal 2 (Frontend):
  ✅ Shows "Compiled successfully!"
  ✅ Browser opened to localhost:3000
  ✅ No compilation errors

Browser:
  ✅ Purple header visible: "Resonance Structure Visualizer"
  ✅ Dropdown menu shows molecules
  ✅ Selecting molecule displays 3D structures
  ✅ Can rotate structures with mouse
  ✅ Can zoom with scroll wheel

-------------------------------------------
Test Full Workflow
-------------------------------------------

1. Open http://localhost:3000
2. Select "Benzene" from dropdown
3. Should see 2 structure cards
4. 3D molecules should be visible and rotatable
5. Element labels (C, H) visible on atoms
6. Click "Back to Selection"
7. Try another molecule

