================================================================================
PART 7: PROJECT STRUCTURE
================================================================================

url/
│
├── backend/                         # Python Flask API
│   ├── venv/                       # Virtual environment (created locally)
│   ├── app.py                      # Flask server, API endpoints
│   ├── molecules.py                # Molecule database (10 molecules)
│   └── requirements.txt            # Python dependencies
│
├── frontend/                        # React web application
│   ├── node_modules/               # NPM packages (created locally)
│   ├── public/
│   │   ├── index.html             # HTML template + 3Dmol.js script
│   │   └── favicon.ico            # Website icon
│   ├── src/
│   │   ├── App.js                 # Main React component
│   │   ├── App.css                # Styling
│   │   ├── MoleculeSelector.js    # Dropdown component
│   │   ├── StructureViewer.js     # 3D visualization component
│   │   └── index.js               # React entry point
│   ├── package.json               # Node dependencies
│   └── package-lock.json          # Locked dependency versions
│
├── .gitignore                      # Files to exclude from Git
└── README.md                       # Project documentation

================================================================================
PART 8: RUNNING THE PROJECT (DAILY USE)
================================================================================

Every time you want to run the project:

-------------------------------------------
Terminal 1 - Start Backend
-------------------------------------------

cd backend
venv\Scripts\activate          # Windows
source venv/bin/activate       # Mac/Linux
python app.py

-------------------------------------------
Terminal 2 - Start Frontend
-------------------------------------------

cd frontend
npm start

Then open browser to: http://localhost:3000

================================================================================
PART 9: TROUBLESHOOTING COMMON ISSUES
================================================================================

-------------------------------------------
Issue: "python not recognized"
-------------------------------------------

Solution:
  - Reinstall Python with "Add to PATH" checked
  - Or use full path: C:\Python3x\python.exe

-------------------------------------------
Issue: "pip not found"
-------------------------------------------

Solution:
  python -m pip install --upgrade pip

-------------------------------------------
Issue: "npm not found"
-------------------------------------------

Solution:
  - Reinstall Node.js from nodejs.org
  - Restart computer after installation

-------------------------------------------
Issue: RDKit installation fails
-------------------------------------------

Solution 1:
  pip install rdkit-pypi

Solution 2:
  pip install rdkit

Solution 3 (Mac with Homebrew):
  brew install rdkit
  pip install rdkit

-------------------------------------------
Issue: "react-scripts not recognized"
-------------------------------------------

Solution:
  cd frontend
  rm -rf node_modules package-lock.json   # Delete and reinstall
  npm install

-------------------------------------------
Issue: Frontend can't connect to backend
-------------------------------------------

Check:
  1. Backend running on port 5000?
  2. Visit: http://localhost:5000/api/molecules
  3. CORS enabled in app.py? (should have Flask-CORS)
  4. Firewall blocking ports?

-------------------------------------------
Issue: 3D molecules not displaying
-------------------------------------------

Check:
  1. Open browser console (F12)
  2. Check for errors
  3. Verify 3Dmol.js loaded: type window.$3Dmol in console
  4. Should return an object, not undefined
  5. Check frontend/public/index.html has 3Dmol script tag

-------------------------------------------
Issue: Port already in use
-------------------------------------------

Backend (port 5000):
  - Close other programs using port 5000
  - Or change port in app.py: app.run(port=5001)

Frontend (port 3000):
  - Press Ctrl+C in frontend terminal
  - Or it will suggest port 3001 automatically

================================================================================
PART 10: UPDATING THE PROJECT
================================================================================

If you pull new changes from GitHub:

Backend:
  cd backend
  venv\Scripts\activate
  pip install -r requirements.txt    # Install new dependencies

Frontend:
  cd frontend
  npm install                         # Install new dependencies

================================================================================
PART 11: SYSTEM REQUIREMENTS
================================================================================

Minimum:
  - OS: Windows 10, macOS 10.15, Ubuntu 20.04 or later
  - RAM: 4 GB
  - Disk: 2 GB free space
  - CPU: Dual-core processor
  - Browser: Chrome 90+, Firefox 88+, Edge 90+, Safari 14+

Recommended:
  - RAM: 8 GB
  - Disk: 5 GB free space
  - CPU: Quad-core processor
  - Internet connection (for npm install)

================================================================================
PART 12: PORTS USED
================================================================================

Port 5000: Flask backend API
Port 3000: React development server

Make sure these ports are not blocked by firewall

================================================================================
PART 13: OFFLINE USAGE
================================================================================

After initial installation:
  ✅ Backend works offline
  ❌ 3Dmol.js requires internet (loaded from CDN)

To make fully offline:
  1. Download 3Dmol-min.js
  2. Save to frontend/public/
  3. Update index.html script src to local file

